class Solution:
    def minInsertions(self, s: str) -> int:
        open_needed = 0
        close_needed = 0

        for ch in s:
            if ch == '(':
                if close_needed % 2 != 0:
                    close_needed += 1
                    open_needed += 1
                close_needed += 2
            else:
                close_needed -= 1
                if close_needed < 0:
                    open_needed += 1
                    close_needed += 2

        return open_needed + close_needed
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass tracks how many '(' and '))' are missing. When ')' is encountered, decrement the expected close_needed; if it goes negative, an '(' is missing. When '(' is encountered, add 2 to close_needed; if an odd count remains, insert one ')' and one '(' to fix.

